Here are the public test cases for feature10_position_and_cursor:
{
  "description": "Exposes reader position tracking for parsed values and cursor-style seeking, position setting, and buffered reads over byte input.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "feature": "pos_value",
        "bytes": "fffefd"
      },
      "expected_output": "status=ok\na=65534\ntracked_pos=2\ninitial_value=253\nmutated_value=1\nclone_value=1\nclone_pos=2\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {
        "feature": "cursor",
        "bytes": "0102030405",
        "start_position": 0,
        "set_position": 0,
        "read_lengths": [
          4,
          4
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "initial_pos=0\nstart_seek=0\nafter_set=0\nread0_len=4\nread0_bytes=1,2,3,4\nread0_pos=4\nread1_len=1\nread1_bytes=5,0,0,0\nread1_pos=5\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the public test cases for feature11_names_and_gates:
{
